Your package masscan failed to build from source in current rawhide.
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12834417
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

Created attachment 1137970 proposed patch
This package FTBFSes because of a gcc-version check which rejects gcc-6.
Upstream seems to have addressed this issue (and more) in later git-versions of this package.
Therefore, I am recommending to upgrade to this package to upstream's git/master in this case. The patch in the attachment contains the diff of masscan.spec of how I would implement it.
Scratch build: http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=13387664
Unless somebody objects, I intend to apply a full update in near future.
